value.title: Nikki Haley says Biden immigration bill will ‘undermine the rule of law’
value.excerpt: Nikki Haley on Tuesday said that President-elect Joe Biden’s plan to give a pathway to citizenship for millions of illegal immigrants would “undermine the rule of law” while also failing to address problems with the asylum system -- a sign of likely Republican opposition to the proposal.

value.title: VP Mike Pence skipping Trump send-off to Florida
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence is not expected to attend Wednesday morning’s farewell ceremony for President Trump at Joint Base Andrews, a source familiar with the vice president’s schedule confirms to Fox News.

value.title: Alice Marie Johnson calls for Trump to pardon nonviolent drug offenders, praises 'unsung hero' Ivanka
value.excerpt: Alice Marie Johnson, the Tennessee grandmother whose life sentence on a federal drug charge was commuted by President Trump, told Fox News Tuesday that the outgoing president should pardon more "nonviolent drug offenders" before Joe Biden is sworn in Wednesday.

value.title: Biden HHS nominee moved mother out of care facility as she directed nursing homes to take COVID patients
value.excerpt: Levine directed Pa. long-term care facilities and nursing homes to accept COVID-19 patients who were unable to return home or who had lived at the facilities prior to their hospitalization.

value.title: Biden Inauguration Day: How many people will attend ceremony in-person?
value.excerpt: The Biden-Harris Inaugural ceremony will be noticeably pared down amid ongoing health and security concerns.

value.title: CBP acting commissioner: Biden sending 'loud and clear' message for migrants
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden has been sending a “loud and clear” message to migrants, who are already heading to the U.S. southern border ahead of his inauguration, Mark Morgan, acting commissioner of U.S. Customs and Border Protection, said on Tuesday.

value.title: Biden DNI nominee Haines says aim should be to 'out-compete China'
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden's nominee for Director of National Intelligence Avril Haines said, if confirmed, she would focus on providing intelligence to support efforts to "out-compete China," while committing to doing more training to educate Americans on the country's malign foreign influence.

value.title: Tiffany Trump announces engagement to Michael Boulos with White House photo, hours before father leaves office
value.excerpt: President Trump's youngest daughter Tiffany Trump and her beau Michael Boulos announced their engagement with a photo taken at the White House on the president's last day in office.

value.title: Army veteran calls out Dem lawmaker for ‘ridiculous’ remark about troops posing threat to Biden
value.excerpt: A West Point graduate and Army veteran ripped Rep. Steve Cohen, D-Tenn., for floating the conspiracy theory that National Guard troops deployed to Washington, D.C., for the inauguration pose a threat to President-elect Joe Biden.

value.title: Huckabee pushes back on calls for 'deprogramming' Trump voters: 'The cult of the left'
value.excerpt: In response to some people claiming Trump supporters need to be "deprogrammed," Fox News contributor Mike Huckabee on Tuesday explained why people voted for the former reality TV star to lead the country.

value.title: Trump rebuts NY Times '1619 Project' with '1776 Report' urging schools to reject 'ideological poison'
value.excerpt: The Trump-backed panel released a 45-page report on the state of American education in what the White House described as a "rebuttal" to "reckless" historical accounts of the country's founding.

value.title: Acting DHS secretary: We want to leave 'no stone unturned' in securing Biden inauguration
value.excerpt: Acting Homeland Security Secretary Peter Gaynor told "America Reports" Monday that there is a "heightened sense of alert" surrounding the security preparations for Joe Biden's inauguration.

value.title: Melania Trump releases farewell message: 'It has been the greatest honor of my life'
value.excerpt: Outgoing first lady Melania Trump reflected on her four years in the White House during a farewell address to the American people on Monday.

value.title: Trump National Garden order includes statues of Whitney Houston, Kobe Bryant, Vince Lombardi, Frank Sinatra
value.excerpt: President Trump issued an executive order on Monday in which he listed dozens of "historically significant" Americans, including entertainers, founding fathers, religious figures, and others, to be featured in the new National Garden of American Heroes.

value.title: Biden’s reported plans to kill Keystone XL pipeline alarm Canadian officials
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden is considering canceling the cross-border permit for TC energy’s Keystone XL pipeline -- and Canadian officials are worried.

value.title: Biden marks MLK Day by volunteering for hunger-relief group
value.excerpt: With an eye toward reuniting the country after the turbulent presidency of Donald Trump, President-elect Joe Biden marked the Martin Luther King Jr. federal holiday by volunteering.

value.title: Biden election legal team takes victory lap, praises help from unions, nonprofits
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden’s legal team on Monday praised help from unions and nonprofits in their efforts to ensure a secure 2020 presidential election, which led to a Biden-Harris victory.

value.title: Trump may issue 50 to 100 commutations, pardons before term ends; rapper Lil Wayne expected to be on list
value.excerpt: President Trump is expected to issue between 50 and 100 commutations and pardons before he leaves office this week, two sources familiar with the list told Fox News.

value.title: Biden aims to 'Make America California Again': paper
value.excerpt: The Los Angeles Times ran a headline Sunday that is sure to grab the attention of Trump supporters everywhere: “Make America California Again? That’s Biden’s plan.”

value.title: Biden transition official tells migrant caravans: 'Now is not the time' to come to US
value.excerpt: An unnamed Biden transition official told NBC News that migrants hoping to claim asylum in the U.S. during the first few weeks of the new administration "need to understand they're not going to be able to come into the United States immediately.

value.title: Washington Republican who backed Trump impeachment faces backlash back home
value.excerpt: Rep. Jaime Herrera Beutler, R-Wash., one of 10 House Republicans who voted to impeach President Trump on charges of "incitement of an insurrection," is facing criticism from her district's conservative base.

value.title: Trump must be barred from post-presidency intelligence briefings: Schiff
value.excerpt: House Intelligence Committee Chairman Rep. Adam Schiff said Sunday that President Trump should be barred from receiving intelligence briefings after he leaves office, an opportunity traditionally extended to former presidents.

value.title: Pence urges Biden administration to have ‘eternal vigilance’ in standing up to China
value.excerpt: In one of his final public appearances before leaving the White House next  week, Vice President Mike Pence urged the Biden administration to exercise "eternal vigilance," especially when it comes to U.S.-China relations.

value.title: AOC says she disagrees with Biden's 'optimistic' view of GOP
value.excerpt: Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez said she disagrees with President-elect Biden on his “optimistic” view of the GOP.

value.title: FBI agent in Trump-Russia's request for 'validation' of Steele reporting denied, left Crossfire Hurricane
value.excerpt: An agent involved in the FBI’s original Trump-Russia case left the Crossfire Hurricane team amid a “professional disagreement” with Bill Priestap, after the former assistant director of counterintelligence denied his request for an “enhanced validation review” of Christopher Steele’s reporting.

value.title: Pence calls Vice President-elect Harris offer congratulations ahead of inauguration
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence called Vice President-elect Kamala Harris on Thursday to discuss the transition of power to the new Biden administration, Fox News has confirmed.

value.title: Cuomo takes parting shot at Trump admin, targets 'reclamation' of SALT funds
value.excerpt: The SALT cap has been one of the bigger thorns in Cuomo's side in recent years.

value.title: Pence front and center in Capitol siege aftermath
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence flew to West Virginia on Friday to attend and speak at a public celebration for the late Air Force Brig. Gen. Chuck Yeager.
